review_blob: Bottle shared with friends after a trip out to eat. Amazing amber color with a thick head that had great lacing. Aromas of hops and bright fruit and caramel. Similar flavors. Full mouthfeel. Pretty good for the style.
Draft at the Brigantine La Mesa. Darker amber. Lots of hope flavor and aroma. Not to bad for what it is.
beer_name: Green Flash Hop Odyssey 30th Street Pale Ale

review_blob: Draft at Brigantine La Mesa. Pale yellow. Classic lager but nothing to get to excited about
beer_name: Anchor Zymaster Series No. 1 California Lager

review_blob: Draft at Brigantine La Mesa. Deep yellow pour with a foamy head. Aromas are malty and bready. Flavors were more pale malt with some golden ale bitterness. Just eh
beer_name: Karl Strauss Brig Brew Golden Ale

review_blob: Bottle at a friends house during a card game. The peach was very up front. Great for a fruit beer. Somewhat of a strange aftertaste that I didnt love
Bottle at friends house during s card game. Lots of hops. Basic but good for an IPA.
Bottle at friends house during a card game. Lots of hops on the aroma and the flavor. Pretty good for an IPA.
Bottle at friends house during a card game. Dark golden pour with small head. Aromas were hops but not amazing. Same for the flavor. Just nothing great here.
Bottle with friends while playing cards. I like this one better than the grapefruit. Which I actually like. Pretty over the IPAs so its good when I can get something interesting and different.
Bottle during cards with friends. Pours hazy golden with a decent head. Hoppy aromas and flavor. Takes two styles I dont like and didnt make them better.
Draft at the brewery. Light golden pour with minimal head. Almost no aroma. Flavor wasnt so bad. Definitely drinkable. The finish is mostly sweet with some bitter citrus.
Draft at the brewery. Reddish pour with little head. Still some lacing. Aromas were decent hops. Flavor was obviously more hops. Some spice. But mostly just hoppy bitterness that was just eh.

Draft at the brewery. Golden amber bordering on orange. Decent head and lacing. Stand by Im upping that appearance by one. Ok. Aromas were sweet hops and syrup. Flavors were more sweet hops and caramel. Bright fruits too. Not bad

Draft at the brewery. Very nice looking beer. Dark golden. Seemed to be dark on top and light on the bottom. But thats where the good part ended. Not much aroma at all. Flavors were smokey at first and I was starting to think everything would be ok. But the flavor went south fast. Heavy bandage. And a bitter aftertaste that didnt fit in.
Draft at the brewery. Great black pour with a smallish head that still left nice lacing. Not much aroma at all but lots of delightful bitter and dark chocolate and coffee flavors.
Draft at the brewery. Brown as expected with almost no head. Aromas were weak but sweet. Sweet flavor that was only slightly as sweet. Some cocoa and nuts. Not bad for a style I really dont like.
beer_name: Pacific Islander Beer (PIB) Tahitian Brown Ale

review_blob: Draft at the brewery in Paso Robles. Yellow clear. Not much head. Ariana of tart fruit bright and tangy. Flavors were similar. More acidic and tart than Wheaty. A good beer.
Draft at the brewery in Paso Robles. Clear yellow with some head left on it. Aromas of grass and apricot. Flavors is more bitter hops and more citrus. Okay for yet another IPA offering.

Draft at the brewery in Paso Robles. Really Im the first rating? Okay. Hazy and dark golden pour with almost no head aromas of spicy wheat and some light banana. Flavors were similar. Pretty good stuff.

Draft at the brewery in Paso Robles. Not as hazy as I had expected for an unfiltered beer but I guess Im used to other styles. Not too bad. Better than i remember DBA being. Kinda wish now that I had done a side by side.
beer_name: Firestone Walker Unfiltered Double Barrel Ale (UDBA)

review_blob: Draft at Taste San Luis Obispo. Nice orange pour with smallish head that still left nice lacing. Lots of hops on the aroma and flavor. Not overly bitter but still hoppy and delicious.

Golden yellow pour out of the bottle at a poker party. The head was very foamy but didnt last. Not much aroma. Some fruity tartness. Flavor was tart but not bitter grapefruit. Not sure why cactus tastes like in beer. Just slightly salty. Not a super amazing gose
Draft at Encontro North Park. Not much aroma off this golden yellow pour that lacked any lasting head. Flavors were better but not much. Sour. Apricot. Strange aftertaste. Eh
Draft at The Brigintine. Pale yellow pour with smallish head. Belgian aromas but the flavor was much happier than I expected. Seemed like a lot of California influence on this Belgian style
From the bottle with friends at a st Patricks day party. Very sour on the aroma and the flavor. Slightly pineapple but mostly acidic sour. Yummy
Bottle at st Patricks day party. Lots of hops and even more grapefruit both aroma and flavor. Not bad

From a 32 oz can at a st Patricks day party. Dark read pour with a decent head. Aromas of lots of peanut butter. Just wow. Flavor was still peanut butter with hops and some bitter in the mix. Not as nice as the aroma. But decent.
Bottle at st Patricks day party. Aromas of hops and citurs. Flavors were the same. Hoppy for an APA. Ok

Bottle shared with friends at q st patricks day party. Clear yellow pour with a decent foamy head. Amazing aromas of bright fruit. Pineapple. Pear. Hoppy citrus. Flavors were not as sweet as the flavors. Hoppy and spice. Clove and horse blanket grassy and floral.
From the bottle at a st Patricks day party. Very dark with a great head. Aromas of nuts and chocolate. Eve more on the aroma. Good stuff.
Dark hazy brown pour from the bottle at a st Patricks day party. Aromas of dark sour fruit. And even sour coconut. Weird but interesting. Flavors are very oaky and still sour. Pretty tasty.
Bottle with friends at st Patricks day party. Aromas were almost just regular Big Eye. But the flavor was kicking with ginger.
beer_name: Ballast Point Big Eye IPA - Ginger

review_blob: From a bottle at a St Patricks day party. Not much aroma but a little sour. Hazy yellow with almost no head that lasted. Flavor was much better with sour and salty noted. A good gose
Draft at Eastbound. Golden yellow por with a disapating head. Hoppy aromas and flavors. So close to an IPA
Draft at Eastbound. Appropriately orange pour with a smallish head. Lots of orange on the aroma and the initial flavor. Bitter ipa finish with a pretty interesting orange after taste.
Draft at eastbound. Golden pour with a decent head. Aromas were nice with lots of light fruit and pear and apricot. Flavors were similar with some bitterness that wasnt as nice as the aroma.
Draft at Oggis. Golden yellow with small foamy head. Aromas of grass and hops. Maltiness comes through on the flavor much more than the happiness. Not too bad.
Draft at Oggis Santee. Dark maroon with almost no head. Aromas are fruity and faintly sour. Flavors were definitely cheery. More sweet than sour. Pretty good.

Draft at Urbn. Really unusual. Strange gray tan color with no head. Not much aroma. Just touches of tartness. Flavor was better. With tart and more strangeness on the finish. Slightly salty. Idk. I kinda like this new (to me) style.
beer_name: Monkey Paw / Marin Funky Sea Monkey

review_blob: Draft at the brewery. Dark Orange brown pour with almost no head. Aromas of heavy oak and barrel. Flavors of more wood and dark fruits. Very alcoholic finish. No surprise with that ABV.
Draft at the brewery. Very pink pour with a minimal head. Aromas are very fruity. Raspberry. Sweet and sour. Fuzzy mouthfeel. The flavor is all sour. Fun raspberry and very light.

Draft at the brewery tonight. Nice deep pour with a tight dark brown/gray head. Looked great. Aromas of sweet mockolate. Flavors were more fake chocolate but a little more bitter than the aroma. Decent chocolate malt finish tho. Really not too bad.
beer_name: Pacific Islander (PIB) Stink Eye Chocolate Stout

review_blob: From the bottle shared with friends. Hops character was there but nothing to excite. Decent.

Draft at the brewery. Hazy yellow pour with an average head. Very very fruity aromas. Pineapple and grapefruit. More grapefruit On the flavor. So much so that I think it was meant to be a Grapefruit Pale Ale. Tasty. I actually liked this beer a lot.
beer_name: Twisted Manzanita Gold Molars Jce Pale

review_blob: Draft at the brewery. Brown pour with a very weak head. Smoke and metal on the nose. More smoke. Bacon. And salmon on the flavor. A little bit of bandage and more metal. I over looked the off flavors and enjoyed this beer.
beer_name: Twisted Manzanita The Rauch that Tipped the Scales

review_blob: Draft at the brewery. Golden and hazy and no head. Just a few bubbles at the top. Lots of sour and lactic acid aromas and flavors. Apricot was more present in the aroma. Flavor was a lot of sour and acidity.
Draft at Oggis Santee. Hazy yellow. Aromas and flavors of wheat twang. About what I expected from an American wheat. Only the Germans do this right.
Draft Oggis Santee. The black pour with a nice head was pretty great. Aromas of wood and bourbon but the flsvors fell off a bit and left thinking it was just ok.
Draft at the Stone Pour it Black Event. Great stuff. Lots of roasty dark fruits and some alcohol on the finish.
Draft at the Stone Pour it Black Event. Great beer. Loved the aromas on this one. Could have smelled it all day.
beer_name: FiftyFifty Imperial Eclipse Stout - Coffee / Java Coffee
